  [Text] Reports reaching us say that heavy fighting took 
place yesterday in the areas of Mutara, Byumba, and Ruhengeri. 
  In the Mutara Zone, our forces inflicted heavy casualties on 
government forces. Some of the government soldiers surrended to 
our forces voluntarily. Many were taken as prisoners of war, 
while others went into disarray. And in Kigali, Presidential 
Guards fired heavy rockets at King Faysal Hospital killing 29 
people and wounding 70 others. This took place on 10 April 
1994, just two days ago. 

