<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The chairman of the IEC [Independent Electoral 
Commission], Mr. Justice Kriegler, says the commission will be 
ready on the 26th this month to take special votes. It will 
also be ready to receive thousands of voters at the 
approximately 9,000 voting stations on the following two days. 
Mr. Justice Kriegler said the location of at least 99 percent 
of the voting stations had already been determined. Mr. 
Kriegler said two plane loads of ballot papers had arrived in 
South Africa from London yesterday and have been taken to places 
of safe-keeping. He called on people, particularly in isolated 
places, to make themselves available to act as monitors at 
voting stations. 

