<H3> <TI>   Heavy Fighting Reported Within ULIMO in Tubmanburg </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Heavy Fighting Reported Within ULIMO in Tubmanburg </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB1304145094 Gbarnga Radio ELRL in English 1400 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB1304145094 </F>
<F P=104>  Gbarnga Radio ELRL </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Heavy fighting is continuing in Tubmanburg, Bomi 
County, between Madingo and Krahn elements within ULIMO [United 
Liberation Movement for Democracy in Liberia]. Alhaji Koromah 
and Roosevelt Johnson recently issued a joint communique in the 
Sierra Leonean capital, Freetown, to stop the bloody conflict 
within the organization. People say the battle for Tubmanburg 
has escalated to other areas in Bomi County. A convoy of relief 
supplies for thousands of citizens in Cape Mount, Bomi, and 
Lower Lofa Counties was stopped at the Po River by ECOMOG 
[Economic Community of West African States Cease-fire Monitoring 
Group] soldiers. 
  Roosevelt Johnson's faction of ULIMO has vowed to revenge 
the 
death of their people killed by the Koromah faction. People say 
ECOMOG soldiers in the Tubmanburg area are being disarmed by the 
Krahn elements of ULIMO. 

</TEXT>

