<H3> <TI>   Government Warns Rwandans Against Killing Citizens </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Warns Rwandans Against Killing Citizens </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB1304113594 Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania Network in Swahili 
0330 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB1304113594 </F>
<F P=104>  Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Swahili </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the press review] </F>
  [Text] A DAILY NEWS front-page story says Tanzania has 
warned warring factions in Rwanda that it won't tolerate the 
killing of any Tanzanians in that country. Dr. Ibrahim Msabaha, 
principal secretary in the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and 
International Cooperation, said yesterday that his government 
will take stern measures against the murder of any Tanzanians by 
any group belonging either to the Rwandan Patriotic Front forces 
or by government forces. 
  He said Tanzania has made great efforts to promote peace in 
Rwanda and would therefore expect its citizens to be accorded 
security and special treatment in that country: We are not 
joking. We would never forgive any side held responsible for the 
death of any Tanzanians in Rwanda. 
  Meanwhile the government has moved to evacuate its citizens 
from Kigali to Bujumbura, Burundi, where the first batch of 20 
evacuees arrived on 10 April. The same story is carried in the 
fifth page of UHURU, which adds that the security of Tanzanians 
in Rwanda should be strictly ensured. 

</TEXT>

