<H4>    RPF Envoy Wants UN Forces To Stay </H4>

<F P=102> LD1304171094 Brussels La Une Radio Network in French 1600 
GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1304171094 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels La Une Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Rwanda Patriotic Front [RPF] would like UN 
Mission in Rwanda [UNAMIR] to stay in Rwanda, and has no 
objection to the presence of Belgian blue helmets in the force. 
We spoke to Jean-Baptiste Ndahumba, RPF spokesman in Brussels: 
  [Begin recording] [Ndahumba] We think that UN forces have to 
stay in Rwanda, UNAMIR must continue its mission, perhaps under 
different circumstances, but we need the help of the 
international community, we need the help of Belgium, which must 
return to our country once security is guaranteed. We want to 
maintain cooperation with the international community and with 
the United Nations. 
  [Unidentified correspondent] So the blue helmets will always 
be welcome? 
  [Ndahumba] They can stay if their security is guaranteed, 
and 
we think that as soon as the foreign nationals have been 
evacuated, we will do everything to bring back peace, order and 
security to Kigali, and to the rest of the country. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

