<H4>    Hutu Radio: Only 500 RPF in Capital </H4>

<F P=102> LD1304192994 Brussels Radio 1 Network in Dutch 1600 GMT 13 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1304192994 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels Radio 1 Network </F>
<F P=105>  Dutch </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In Rwanda, the extremist Hutu station Radio des 
Milles Collines denies the Patriotic Front's offensive. In the 
past few weeks this radio station has been responsible for the 
anti-Belgain witch-hunt. The Hutu station says that the rebels 
are still 80 km from Kigali. 
  There are only some 500 rebels in the capital, a Radio des 
Milles Collines journalist says. According to him, the 
government army can deal with them without difficulty: 
  [Begin unidentified correspondent recording, in French] Some 
of them have been killed by us, some have hidden. To be frank I 
can assure you that there are no more than 500 of them [words 
indistinct] the groups retreat, they shoot at night. Well then, 
we will seek them out and crush them. There is another group 
which has retreated and is hidden but there is no battle which 
it has engaged in, there is no assault. The Patriotic Front has 
come from positions. [end recording] 
  Radio des Milles Collines is managed by a Belgian from 
Liege. 
Minister Clases has already protested against the station's 
anti-Belgian broadcasts. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

