<H4>    Kigali Reportedly About To Fall to RPF </H4>

<F P=102> LD1304220194 Paris Radio France International in French 2130 
GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1304220194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio France International </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Fighting has continued throughout the day in Rwanda. 
The Rwanda Patriotic Front forces coming from the north have 
managed to link up with the 600 rebels in central Kigali, but 
they have not yet taken control of the city. The rebels said a 
moment ago that they control four strategic points in Kigali. 
Christophe Boisbouvier has just filed this report: 
  [Begin Boisbouvier recording] With the rebels coming from 
the 
north linking up with those who were holed up in central Kigali, 
the regular army now finds itself surrounded in the presidency 
district. Unless there is significant resistance from the 
civilian population which has set up roadblocks in the streets, 
the fall of Kigali seems imminent. It might, however, be more 
difficult for the rebels to take the northern strongholds of 
Byumba and Ruhengeri, since the government forces there are well 
armed with artillery. 
  The rebels will, however, have to be wary of their success. 
In statements today, they gave assurances that they would not 
confiscate the state for the Tutsi minority. The Rwandan people 
will judge them on their actions. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

