<F P=100> CENTRAL AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Rwanda </F>
<H3> <TI>   Liberal Party Denounces Government, Massacres </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Liberal Party Denounces Government, Massacres </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1304163194 (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura in English to 
Rwanda 1100 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1304163194 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement issued by the Liberal Party; place and date not </F>
given] 
  [Text] Due to the current crisis in our country, caused by 
elements who are opposed to the Arusha peace agreement, the 
Liberal Party [PL] is saddened by the death of President 
Habyarimana and the death of the president of Burundi, Cyprien 
Ntaryamira, who died on 5 April 1994. The Liberal Party 
denounces the massacres in Kigali and the rest of the country. 
The massacres perpetuated by Presidential Guards, MRND 
[Republican National Movement for Democracy and Development] 
youthwingers and some elements of the Army. The killings 
targeted members of the opposition and people of Tutsi origin. 
They killed the prime minister, Mrs. Agathe Uwilingiyimana, 
cabinet ministers, and opposition leaders. It is clear that the 
massacres had been planned earlier on. 
  The PL denounces the so-called government that has been 
announced in Kigali, a government that is founded on the 
massacre of more than 20,000 people in Kigali alone. A 
government that was formed in disregard of the national 
Constitution. The PL denounces the murdering of Landouald 
Ndasingwa, formerly the first vice president of the Liberal 
Party and the other members of the Liberal Party who have been 
murdered. The PL denounces Mr. Justin Mugenzi and his clique 
who are trying to hijack the Liberal Party and join the 
illegitimate government that has been announced in Rwanda. 
  The current crisis in Rwanda is the implementation of a plan 
that has been hatched for some time. The plan is now 
implemented by murderers who have killed opposition leaders and 
people of Tutsi origin. This trend of killing has continued 
since the war started. These killers should be made to answer 
for their crimes. 
  The PL requests all the opposition parties in Rwanda, the 
international community, and all peace-loving people to join 
hands and fight the enemies of peace and democracy in Rwanda. 
  Signed by Kayiranga Esdras, Higiro Prosper, Musengimana 
Joseph. These are some of the surviving leaders of the Liberal 
Party. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

