  [Text] Kinshasa, 13 Apr (AFP) -- Casimir Bizimungu, former 
Rwandan public health minister, and his higher education 
colleague arrived in Kinshasa today from Goma (eastern Zaire) 
after fleeing the trouble taking place in their country. This 
was learned from reliable sources today in the Zairian capital. 
  According to eyewitnesses who saw them at the Ndjili 
airport, 
they were welcomed by Etienne Sigigera, the Rwandan ambassador 
in Kinshasa. The two former ministers, who were at the Kigali 
airport on 6 April waiting for the aircraft bringing back the 
Rwandan and Burundian presidents, had to flee towards Zaire when 
confusion followed the assassination. 

