<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mediation Efforts `Collapse' Over Preconditions </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meyer Meets With Mediators </H4>

<F P=102> MB1404101094 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0946 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1404101094 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg April 14 SAPA -- Constitutional 
Development Minister Roelf Meyer was meeting international 
mediator Henry Kissinger for talks on Thursday [14 April] 
morning aimed at salvaging the embattled mediation process. Mr 
Meyer's meeting was one of several being held with the mediators. 
  Mr Meyer would not be drawn on what his meeting was about, 
but the parties are trying to settle their differences on the 
terms of reference so that mediation can get underway. 
  The international mediation forum said in a statement that 
mediators were still in contact with the parties. They have 
apparently given the parties until lunchtime on Thursday to 
settle their differences on the terms of reference. 

</TEXT>

