<F P=106> [Statement issed by International Mediation Forum on the </F>
SAPA PR Wire Service on 14 April] 
  [Text] After an evening of separate sessions with the three 
parties, the mediators are currently meeting to determine the 
way ahead. The mediators are still in contact with the parties. 
  The mediators would like to make it clear that queries have 
been raised regarding fees the mediators may have been paid in 
order to participate in the mediation process. No fees have been 
asked for and none have been paid. The mediators are 
participating on the basis of a commitment to a peaceful 
settlement of the constitutional differences of the parties and 
a sense of goodwill. 
  You will be advised of further developments during the day. 

