BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by G. van Oudtshoorn] </F>
  [Text] Bisho April 13 SAPA -- Four prominent members of 
former Ciskei military ruler Brig Oupa Gqozo's African 
Democratic Movement [ADM] have withdrawn as candidates for the 
elections, SABC [South African Broadcasting Corporation] radio 
news reoported on Wednesday. 
  ADM Publicity Secretary Vuyani Mati confirmed the 
resignations from the movement, naming the men as: Ciskei 
Department of Information Assistant Director Namba Sebe; ADM's 
former Publicity Secretary Vuyo Magodla; Ciskei consul general 
in Johannesburg Mthetheleli Taba; and Department of Information 
Acting Director Nolwandle Ngxizela. 
  Earlier this week Ciskei's joint administrators announced 
that employed political candidates would have to take unpaid 
leave during the election period. 

