<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   TEC Supports Halt to Sales of State Land </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    TEC Supports Halt to Sales of State Land </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1404071694 Johannesburg SAPA in English 2338 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1404071694 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pretoria April 13 SAPA -- A halt on sales of state 
land was on Wednesday [13 April] called for by the Transitional 
Executive Council's [TEC] sub-council on regional/local 
government and traditional authorities. In a statement, the 
sub-council said it had decided to ask the government to stop 
the sale of state land without first consulting the sub-council. 
  On the sale of state land in kwaNdebele, the sub-council 
decided that no land be disposed of unless in exceptional 
circumstances and specially not through the process being 
planned by the homeland government; that sales, when necessary, 
be transparent and based on consensus; that the process of 
township development proceed on the basis that no decision be 
taken on entitlement of occupation or ownership; and that the 
process of establishing the identities of people living on the 
land in kwaNdebele proceed on the basis that it not involve 
decisions on who will be entitled to occupation or ownership. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

