<H3> <TI>   Finance Minister Leaves for Marrakech GATT Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Finance Minister Leaves for Marrakech GATT Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1404064894 Johannesburg SAPA in English 2256 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1404064894 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pretoria April 13 SAPA -- Finance and Trade and 
Industry Minister Derek Keys departed Wednesday [13 April] 
evening for Marrakech, Morocco to formally sign the Uruguay 
Round of the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade. Mr Keys is 
accompanied by African National Congress National Executive 
Committee member Professor Kadar Asmal, of the organisation's 
international affairs wing, and officials from the Trade and 
Industry Department. 
  A Finance Ministry statement said Mr Keys was expected to 
meet with senior officials and government ministers from other 
GATT member countries. He would sign GATT's Uruguay Round treaty 
on Friday at the formal ceremony. 

