<F P=101> Lesotho </F>
<H3> <TI>   Names of Abducted Ministers Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Names of Abducted Ministers Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1404121994 Maseru Radio Lesotho in English 1130 GMT 14 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1404121994 </F>
<F P=104>  Maseru Radio Lesotho </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The speaker of the National Assembly, Dr. J.T. 
Kolane, this morning adjourned the house until tomorrow after he 
informed the members that some members of parliament had been 
abducted by armed soldiers. Dr. Kolane said he was of the 
opinion that the members could not concentrate on debates under 
these circumstances. The speaker said he was disappointed by 
these despicable acts. Although the speaker did not mention the 
names of the members concerned, it is believed that they are the 
deputy prime minister, the Honorable Selometsi Baholo; the 
honorable minister of justice, Mr. Kelebone Maope; the minister 
of trade and industry, the Honorable Shakhane Mokhehle; the 
minister of education, the Honorable Pakalitha Mosisili; and the 
minister of natural resources, the Honorable Monyane Moleleki. 
  It is understood that the ministers were arrested at their 
homes and offices, but there have been no details of the 
circumstances of their arrests. 

</TEXT>

