<F P=100> EAST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Somalia </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Contingent Blocks Offensive, Hand Over Attackers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Contingent Blocks Offensive, Hand Over Attackers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1404184294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1620 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1404184294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 14 Apr (MENA)-- The Egyptian force taking 
part in the UN peacekeeping forces in Somalia checked an 
offensive by an armed Somali group against a UN ammunition depot 
southwest of Mogadishu airport on 12 April. 
  An official military source today stated that the Egyptian 
force fired warning shots to deter the attackers. To deter the 
repeated attempts against the depot, it had to surround the 
group members and engaged them in a 35-minute clash, after which 
they surrendered. 
  The source added that the Egyptian force turned the group 
members, who numbered 19, over to the Somali police, adding that 
the Egyptian force sustained no losses. 
  Defense and War Production Minister Field Marshal Muhammad 
Husayn Tantawi thanked the commander, officers, and soldiers of 
the Egyptian force in Somalia for their vigilance and good 
performance. 
  The UN commander in Somalia also thanked the Egyptian force 
for its distinguished performance in frustrating an attempt to 
seize the UN ammunition. 

</TEXT>

