<H3> <TI>   People Continue To Flee Kigali </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    People Continue To Flee Kigali </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1404213294 (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura in French to 
Rwanda 1815 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1404213294 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Instead of a truce, the noose is tightening 
round the criminals, especially in the capital, where people are 
fleeing the fighting en masse and also because they are 
expecting a final assault to take place soon after the departure 
of all [foreign] nationals and UNAMIR [UN Assistance Mission in 
Rwanda] Blue Berets. Indeed, many people have already left the 
capital in a hurry. [passage omitted] 
  Other people who have fled have done so because of fears 
that 
they will have to account for the atrocities committed against 
innocent people. In this regard, those who were involved in 
organizing the events have cleared off with their families. For 
instance, reports say that 200 people are stuck at Bujumbura 
international airport waiting to be evacuated to France. They 
have asked France to grant them asylum. Burundi gave them 36 
hours to allow France to decide their case. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

