<F P=100> CENTRAL AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Rwanda </F>
<H3> <TI>   Soldiers Said Hiding Among Refugees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Soldiers Said Hiding Among Refugees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1404134994 (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura in Kinyarwanda to 
Rwanda 0950 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1404134994 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura </F>
<F P=105>  Kinyarwanda </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Some soldiers are removing their military uniforms 
and hiding among Rwandan refugees in Uganda. They are hiding 
among refugees. It is understandable for one to take refuge, 
especially if one does not want to assist the Rwandan Patriotic 
Front [RPF] combatants in fighting the war. However, it is not 
understable for one to take refuge and hide one's identity. How 
would one know there is no other objective? 
  Why do the soldiers want to hide among civilians? We have 
spoken on several occasions about the mistreatment of people in 
our country. Enemies hide where civilians are taking refuge and 
then start killing them. There is that possibility. 
  Let us hope that the government forces who are fleeing and 
hiding do not have such plans. They should not try to hide. 
They should wear their military uniforms while in hiding. 
There is war so they can flee but they should present 
themselves to the Ugandan authorities who will show them where 
to stay. They should not stay in the country disguised as 
civilians. It is better for them to identify themselves rather 
than to disguise themselves. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-717 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drafr073_a_94014" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-AFR-94-073 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  14 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> CENTRAL AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Rwanda </F>
<H3> <TI>   RPF Rejects Proposal for Talks With `Another Side' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    RPF Rejects Proposal for Talks With `Another Side' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1404132994 (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura in Kinyarwanda to 
Rwanda 1015 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1404132994 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura </F>
<F P=105>  Kinyarwanda </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign radio stations said this morning that talks 
have been planned between the Rwandan Patriotic Front [RPF] and 
another side. Some have been misled to say that the RPF might 
meet the government. Which government? Major General Romeo 
Dallaire for his part said on BBC radio that the talks will be 
between soldiers at the front and troop commanders at the front. 
He added that the talks are low level. Maj. Gen. Dallaire did 
not say what the aim of the talks is. 
  There are two things which must be explained: Which people 
will the RPF meet and what is the aim of the talks? We refer 
here to those who may wrongly think that the talks concern a 
cease-fire. Going back to the first point, who will the RPF talk 
to? There are soldiers who have dissociated themselves from the 
clique of killers. These soldiers, in addition to meeting the 
RPF, even said they could work together with the RPF to plan how 
to get rid of the clique of killers. On the other side, there 
are soldiers and politicians who are part of the clique, for 
example government members. They cannot all hold talks with the 
RPF. The clique is the one which kills; it is the one the RPF 
is fighting, and the RPF will only relax once it has saved 
Rwandans from it. Therefore those who can meet the RPF and who 
can work with it are the ones who have distanced themselves from 
the clique. 
  Even the talks would not be aimed at stopping the war. The 
talks would rather be aimed at removing the case for resuming 
the war. The reason for resuming war is that the Presidential 
Guards continue to kill innocent people, and the Republican 
National Movement for Democracy and Development militia continue 
to bereave the country in all corners. There are people like 
Rugambarara from (Bicyumbi) commune who have massacred people. 
Therefore the talks would be aimed at restoring peace to the 
country. 
  This is one of the reasons why the RPF has resumed fighting. 
To restore peace in the country means annihilating the killers; 
to defeat the enemies of peace means continuing the fight until 
they are defeated. So, even if the talks took place, they would 
not be about a cease-fire but rather to form a coalition to 
fight the enemies of peace so that they are completely defeated. 
That means that they would be held between the RPF and those 
who have distanced themselves from the clique. We have always 
said that soldiers who really believe they are Rwandan soldiers 
should distance themselves from the clique of presidential 
guards and work together with the RPF. Many of these soldiers 
have always distanced themselves from the clique. They should 
show their courage and love for the motherland by officially 
declaring that they are with the RPF. Rwandans will thank them 
for that. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-718 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drafr073_a_94015" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-AFR-94-073 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  14 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> CENTRAL AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Rwanda </F>
<H3> <TI>   MDR Leader Issues Statement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MDR Leader Issues Statement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1404161994 (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura in Kinyarwanda to 
Rwanda 1015 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1404161994 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura </F>
<F P=105>  Kinyarwanda </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Communique issued by Faustin Twagiramungu, prime </F>
minister-designate and president of the Republican Democratic 
Movement on 13 April; place not given] 
  [Excerpts] Members of Republican Democratic Movement [MDR] 
and Rwandans. Peace be with you and continue to trust God, as 
the truth will finally win out. Rwandans, the death of His 
Excellency President Juvenal Habyarimana has not yet been 
explained. Some continue to say, without evidence, that he was 
killed by the Rwandan Patriotic Front [RPF], while others are 
saying that enemies of the country were responsible. Let us 
hope that the truth will finally be known. [passage omitted] 
  How can we hold talks with the people who killed Prime 
Minister Agathe Uwilingiyimana, who was the president of the MDR 
in Butare, who was the people's mother, an intellectual, a 
nationalist? How can we hold talks with these killers? How can 
we hold talks with the murderers of Frederic Nzamurambaho, the 
minister of agriculture and livestock and the national president 
of the Social Democratic Party, a father of all who was a 
peace-loving person. How can we hold talks with those who 
killed Felicien Ngango, the first vice president of Christian 
Democratic Party [PDC] at the national level, an intellectual, 
and a Rwandan who knew the law. [passage omitted] 
  We shall never hold talks with those who killed Faustin 
Nucogoza, who was the minister of information and president of 
the MDR in Byumba. He was a fearless man who loved democracy. 
All those who were killed joined others who were killed earlier 
by those murderers. They took the lives of Mayuya, Gapyisi, 
Gatabazi and others. The killings show and identify who is 
Rwanda's enemy. 
  The ethnic war that the killers wanted to launch in the 
country is not acceptable to us. Were all the above-mentioned 
people who died killed by Tutsis? One cannot say that the RPF 
waged a war because of the killings. We should understand and 
explain to the people that the RPF did not attack, but came to 
the rescue of the people to stop the killers from shedding blood. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-719 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drafr073_a_94016" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-AFR-94-073 </AU>
