<F P=101> Rwanda </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Urges Mobilization Against Rebels </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Urges Mobilization Against Rebels </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1504105094 Paris Radio France International in French 0900 
GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1504105094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio France International </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Rwanda is enduring a wait. The capital, Kigali, is 
waiting to see one of the two sides gain the upper hand. It 
does not appear that the troops of the Rwandan Patriotic Front 
[RPF] have taken complete control of the town. So far, they 
have dug trenches along a frontline in the center of town. This 
morning, the government radio called on the people to mobilize 
against those who want to take power, I quote. 
  The United Nations Assistance Mission in Rwanda is 
continuing 
its contacts with the warring sides to attempt to get them to 
meet. Meanwhile, the French and Belgian paratroopers are waiting 
for a period of calm at the airport in order to be able to 
repatriate their nationals. 
  The International Committee of the Red Cross has announced 
that it has lost 30 employees; as for UNICEF, it has lost 7 of 
its employees. 

</TEXT>

