<F P=100> CENTRAL AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Rwanda </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Assures Security of UN Observers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Ministry Assures Security of UN Observers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB1504103994 Lome Radio Lome in French 0600 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB1504103994 </F>
<F P=104>  Lome Radio Lome </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Communique issued by the National Defense Ministry; place </F>
and date not given] 
  [Text] In line with the implementation of UN Security 
Council Resolution 872 of 5 October 1993 under which the council 
established the UN Assistance Mission in Rwanda [UNAMIR], our 
country, Togo, was requested by the United Nations to send two 
contingents to Rwanda. The first contingent comprising military 
observers has been operating in Rwanda since December 1993. The 
second detachment meant for the UN civil police has been on 
mission in Rwanda since January. The Togolese Armed Forces High 
Command is in permanent contact with UN and UNAMIR officials. 
  Following the recent painful events in Rwanda following the 
assassination of the Rwandan and Burundian presidents, the 
United Nations has taken measures to ensure the security of all 
UNAMIR contingents. At the moment, we can assert that the 
situation of our detachments in Rwanda does not give cause for 
concern. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

