<H3> <TI>   RPF Reiterates Evacuation Deadline, `Consequences' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    RPF Reiterates Evacuation Deadline, `Consequences' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1404212594 (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura in English to 
Rwanda 1835 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1404212594 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement issued by the RPA; place and date not given] </F>
  [Text] 1. The Rwandese Patriotic Army [RPA] would like to 
remind the international community on the communique signed on 
12th April 1994 at 0700 hours local time between the Rwandese 
Patriotic Front [RPF] on one hand and UNAMIR [UN Assistance 
Mission in Rwanda], on the other, that the evacuation of foreign 
nationals should be completed on 14th April 1994 at 0700 hours 
local time. 
  2. The evacuation of foreign troops should be completed on 
14th April 1994 at 1900 hours local time, after the evacuation 
of their nationals. 
  3. Any aircraft or troops entering the territory of Rwanda 
after midnight local time, 14th April 1994, stand the risk of 
being considered hostile and as such vulnerable. The RPF will 
not be held responsible for the consequences. Signed, (Andrew 
Ruygemba), lieutenant colonel, secretary, RPA high command. 

</TEXT>

