<H3> <TI>   Foreign Troops Given 24 Hours To Complete Evacuation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Troops Given 24 Hours To Complete Evacuation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1504110194 Brussels Radio 1 Network in Dutch 1000 GMT 15 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1504110194 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels Radio 1 Network </F>
<F P=105>  Dutch </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The United Nations says that foreign troops in 
Rwanda will be given another 24 hours to evacuate foreigners. 
The United Nations has made new agreements with the Patriotic 
Front and with government units. Previously, the Patriotic 
Front had said that the evacuation operation had to be over by 
yesterday evening. There are about five Belgian citizens left 
in Rwanda. Apart from that, there are 10 journalists at Kigali 
airport. 
  In the meantime, about 200 Belgian paratroopers have arrived 
in Kenya. In the course of the day as many other soldiers as 
possible will be withdrawn from Rwanda -- their exact number 
depends on the circumstances on the spot. 

</TEXT>

