  [Text] Maseru April 15 SAPA -- Several bursts of what is 
believed to be automatic rifle fire were heard early Friday [15 
April] morning in Lesotho's capital, Maseru, where troops on 
Thursday shot dead Deputy Prime Minister Selometsi Baholo and 
took four cabinet ministers hostage for a day. 
  It was not clear who was firing or at whom and there was no 
