BFN 

  [Text] Vice chairman of the Liberian National Transitional 
Government, Mr. Isaac Musa, today paid a courtesy call on the 
field commander of the multiafrican peacekeeping force in 
Liberia, Major General John Inienger, at his free zone office in 
Monrovia. During the visit, which lasted for an hour, Vice 
Chairman Musa reiterated the NPFL [National Patriotic Front of 
Liberia]'s commitment to peace and the Cotonou accord. He 
however expressed surprise at recent harassment and intimidation 
being meted against citizens plying the road from Gbarnga to 
Monrovia by the Nigerian contingent and ULIMO [United Liberation 
Movement for Democracy in Liberia]. 

