<H3> <TI>   Abacha Reportedly Orders Release of Editors </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Abacha Reportedly Orders Release of Editors </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB1404222594 Lagos NTA Television Network in English 2000 
GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB1404222594 </F>
<F P=104>  Lagos NTA Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] From news just coming in, the head of state, 
General Sani Abacha, has ordered the immediate release of the 
three NEWSWATCH editors, Ray Ekpu, Yakubu Mohamed, and Dan 
Agbese. According to a statement just reaching us from the 
office of the chief press secretary to the head of state, the 
order was given after representations to the government by 
newspaper proprietors, the Nigerian Press Organization, and the 
NUJ [Nigerian Union of Journalists] on the media press briefing 
of Gen. Abacha in Abuja today. According to the statement, the 
order marks a new beginning in government-media relations built 
on mutual respect, understanding, and the pursuit of positive 
national goals and objectives. 

</TEXT>

