<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Guy Rogers] </F>
  [Text] Johannesburg April 15 SAPA -- The Freedom Front [FF] 
says Thursday's [14 April] TV debate between President F W de 
Klerk and ANC President Nelson Mandela was a microcosm of South 
Africa's present politics -- "an NP[National Party]-ANC go it 
alone show". 
  The debate was a sterile shadow-boxing contest, the FF said. 
"History will show the NP-ANC relationship is similar to that of 
the blackwidow spider using and discarding its mate..." 
  The African National Congress would discard the NP once a 
transfer of power had been completed, the FF said. 

</TEXT>

