<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The African National Congress says it would like 
officials from the Persian Gulf to attend Mr. Nelson Mandela's 
presidential inauguration in the event of an ANC victory in this 
month's elections. During a brief visit to Kuwait, ANC National 
Chairman Thabo Mbeki said that he has extended provisional 
invitations on visits to Qatar, Kuwait, and the United Arab 
Emirates this week. Mr. Mbeki met Kuwait's Foreign Ministry 
Under Secretary Sulayman al-Shahin [words in distinct]. 

