<H3> <TI>   Viljoen Urges Inclusion of CP, IFP in Election </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Viljoen Urges Inclusion of CP, IFP in Election </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1504101694 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in English 0500 
GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1504101694 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Freedom Front has called on all parties apart 
from the National Party and the ANC to participate in a joint 
meeting at which a demand for the postponement of the election 
would be formulated. Party leader Constand Viljoen told a 
public meeting in Kraaifontein in the Western Cape last night 
that the aim was to ensure that the IFP [Inkatha Freedom Party] 
and the Conservative Party [CP] could also be included in the 
poll. 
  [Begin recording] [Correspondent James Barkhuizen] The 
Kraaifontein meeting was the biggest so far on the Freedom Front 
election tour. General Viljoen told more than 1,500 supporters 
that election in the present climate of violence and without the 
IFP was unthinkable. He said the smaller parties would urgently 
have to consider the fairness of the election. 
  [Viljoen, in progress]...and if we decide that it is not the 
case, then we should put a joint case to the Independent 
Electoral Commission to say that we smaller parties, with the 
exclusion of the ANC and the National Party, we feel that this 
is not a free and fair situation. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

