<H3> <TI>   ANC Demands Withdrawal of David Duke Visa </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ANC Demands Withdrawal of David Duke Visa </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1504061494 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0102 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1504061494 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by S. Denny] </F>
  [Text] Johannesburg April 14 SAPA -- The African National 
Congress [ANC] on Thursday [14 April] demanded the immediate 
withdrawal of the visa of visiting American David Duke, a former 
member of the Ku Klux Klan and avowed right-winger. Mr Duke, a 
former U.S. congressional candidate, arrived in South Africa on 
Tuesday on a private visit. 
  "His purpose here seems to be to stoke up the war psychosis 
which has already been ignited by a broad coalition of black and 
white right-wing extremists," the ANC said in a statement in 
Johannesburg. 
  "He said on his arrival there had not been 300 years of 
oppression (in South Africa), but years of opportunity. 
  "This country would be better off without this sort of 
malicious meddling in our affairs," the ANC said. South Africans 
did not need Mr Duke, the ANC said, adding that he should not be 
given time on radio or television to air his "noxious" views. 
  "The ANC demands the immediate withdrawal of his visit 
permit 
to South Africa." 

</TEXT>

