<H3> <TI>   Situation in Bophuthatswana Said Worsening </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Situation in Bophuthatswana Said Worsening </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1404161494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1400 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1404161494 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The situation in Bophuthatswana is reported to be on 
the brink of going out of control. A co-administrator of the 
homeland, Mr. Job Mokgoro, said after a meeting with the 
Bophuthatswana police in Mmabatho that law and order was 
threatened and that this could affect the elections in the 
territory. Mr. Mokgoro said the TEC [Transitional Executive 
Council] had been informed of the deteriorating situation in the 
homeland. Reacting to rumors that certain police members loyal 
to the deposed government were regrouping to disrupt the 
election in the homeland. He said the police were investigating 
the situation. 

</TEXT>

