<F P=105>  Kinyarwanda </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today's news also concerns the flight of the clique 
of killers, who are currently stuck at Burundi International 
Airport. Let us recall who they are: There is Ferdinand 
Nahimana, whom you know, who was minister of higher education 
and scientific research. He belongs to the Republican National 
Movement for Democracy and Development-Coalition for the Defense 
of the Republic [MRND-CDR] and is known for dividing Rwandans. 
He made this the law of Rwanda and the law became MRND ideology. 
  You also know Simeon Nteziryayo, minister at the Presidency. 
He was too powerful in the office of the president recently. 
There is Cyprien Munyankundu, secretary general of the National 
Assembly that was imposed by the president. The head of the 
deputies, Theodore Sindikubwayo, is the one who imposed himself 
as president of the Republic. 
  There is Faustin Ruzindana, (Fidel Ntuyenabo), and Supreme 
Court President Alphonse Marie Nkubito, who is among those who 
fought for change, who fought the dictatorship. He escaped the 
presidential guard killers. 
  There is also Lieutenant Colonel Charles Uwihoreye and Mrs. 
Casimir Bizimungu, wife of former Health Minister Casimir 
Bizimungu, who is a staunch member of the MRND-CDR. He is not 
in Burundi; he fled to Zaire. There is Daniel Mbangura who was 
minister of higher education and scientific research. You know 
him. He belongs to the MRND-CDR. There is Mrs. Deo Nsabimana, 
wife of Major General Deo Nsabimana, who was chief of staff of 
the Rwandan Armed Forces. He died in the crash with the Rwandan 
and Burundi presidents on 6 April. There is Mrs. Sylvestre 
Nsanzimana, wife of the former prime minister of the first 
coalition government and Mrs. Pascal Ndengejeho, wife of 
Ndengejeho of the Republican democratic movement, who is known 
to have refused to take part in the government of the late 
Agathe Uwilingiyimana. There is Mrs. Faustin Maniraho, Mrs. 
Felicien Kabuga, wife of Kabuga, head of the divisionist 
Radio-Television Libre des Milles Collines radio, and Mrs. 
Ntagerura, wife of former Transport and Communications Minister 
Ntagerura, a staunch MRND-CDR member. All these people have 
fled. 
  So, the clique of killers has fled along with its families. 
The clique which started the war has fled. They have left the 
Rwandan youth they sent to war behind. Those who are still 
fighting for the clique, why are you fighting now that those you 
fought for have left you at the front? What is the relationship 
between you and those who left you at the war front? Unite with 
the Rwandan Patriotic Front [RPF] to search for all those who 
supported the clique wherever they are, whether in the communes 
of (Bicumbi), Gikoro, and elsewhere. 

</TEXT>

