<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   NP: De Klerk `Clear Winner' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NP: De Klerk `Clear Winner' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1504053594 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0451 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1504053594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement issued by the National Party Federal Council on </F>
14 April on the SAPA PR Wire Service] 
  [Text] 
<H5>  President F W de Klerk, clear winner of TV debate </H5>
  President F W de Klerk was the undoubted winner of tonights 
debate, particularly on all questions about the future of South 
Africa. He had the clearest view of where the country is going 
and demonstrated he has the experience to get us there. 
  He gave a performance which was decisive, showed his mastery 
of the facts, and was compelling in setting out the 
transformation that has taken place in the new national party. 
  By contrast Mr Mandela, was generalised and sometimes vague. 
He dwelt too much on the past, and had very little to offer when 
it came to the hard questions about the economy. He was also 
more intent on scoring cheap debating points than addressing the 
real issues. It was alarming to see his finger-wagging style 
when he ran out of arguments. 
  This election is about the future not the past. Clearly 
President de Klerk and the new National Party are the ones to 
lead us there. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

